+// TracedReferenceReuse). Unlike the zap values above, these are written into
+// the `object_` slot of a node that is still *in use*, so they must be
+// Smi-shaped (low bit clear). This way the marker and young-generation code
+// treat them as non-heap values and skip them, exactly like kNullAddress. They
+// are chosen with non-zero lower 32 bits so that on 64-bit they can never
